# PART 2: MARKET RESEARCH & VALIDATION\par
\par
## 2.1 The India Camping Market \emdash  Numbers That Matter\par
\par
The India Camping Equipment Market size was valued at around USD 892 million in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 2,027 million by 2030. The market is estimated to grow at a CAGR of around 14.66% during the forecast period, i.e., 2025\endash 30.\par
\par
This is just **equipment**. The actual market for camping experiences, stays, and outdoor hospitality is layered on top of this. The platform layer \emdash  which is what CampIn occupies \emdash  is currently almost entirely unorganized and uncaptured in India.\par
\par
The India Camping Equipment Market growth is due to the increasing inclination of consumers towards outdoor recreational activities, increasing investments in tourism, advancement in technologies, and encouragement of environmentally friendly alternatives. The rising number of travelers is due to affordable camping packages and social media connectivity among the young generation, especially millennials and Gen-Z.\par
\par
India also witnessed a spike in camping in 2024.\par
\par
Government initiatives such as the Swadesh Darshan Scheme and a growing adventure travel culture are driving equipment demand \emdash  and by extension, the demand for places to actually camp.\par
\par
Rapid urbanization, increasing disposable incomes, and changing consumer lifestyles are driving demand for leisure and recreational activities, including camping, hiking, and nature-based tourism, in urban and semi-urban areas across India. Rising domestic and international tourism, coupled with growing interest in adventure travel and experiential tourism, are fueling demand for camping experiences among Indian travelers seeking authentic and offbeat experiences.\par
\par
**The verdict: The market is real, growing fast, and woefully underserved by platforms. CampIn is entering at exactly the right time.**\par
\par
---\par
\par
## 2.2 The Van Life & Campervan Culture in India \emdash  A Hidden Gold Mine\par
\par
With the rise of remote work, the hunger for offbeat destinations, and the fatigue from rigid itineraries, more Indians are turning to camper vans to rewrite their travel stories.\par
\par
The van life movement is no longer confined to the West. In the past few years, India has seen a fascinating shift in how people approach travel. What began as a niche concept is now turning into a cultural movement among millennials, adventure seekers, and even families.\par
\par
Caravan camping is gaining immense popularity in India as adventurous travelers embrace the freedom of life on the road. From self-converted vans to luxury caravans, these nomads are redefining travel by exploring the country's hidden gems on wheels.\par
\par
The single biggest unsolved problem for this growing community? **Where to stop safely overnight.** Caravan holidays and the experience of RV/campervan/motorhome is a new culture to which Indians are waking up after the Corona Pandemic. Yet there is **no organized platform** helping them find safe stops with water, washrooms, electricity, and trusted hosts. CampIn fills this vacuum.\par
\par
