# PART 4: THE CAMPIN BUSINESS MODEL \f2\emdash  VALIDATED\par
\par
## 4.1 Core Model: The Two-Sided Marketplace\par
\par
CampIn is a **Hipcamp-style, Airbnb-structured, India-first outdoor platform.** The model is validated globally by Hipcamp and locally by the early traction of HireACamp and CampMonk \emdash  but neither has executed it to its full potential in India.\par
\par
### How the model works:\par
\par
```\par
HOST (Farm/Terrace/Forest/Land Owner)\par
   \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Lists space for free\par
\f2    \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Sets price + amenities\par
\f2    \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Manages bookings\par
   \par
CAMPIN PLATFORM (The Marketplace)\par
\f2    \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Discovery + trust layer\par
\f2    \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Takes 10% from host per booking\par
\f2    \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Charges 5-8% service fee from camper\par
   \par
CAMPER (Traveler/Road Tripper/Vanlifer)\par
\f2    \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Discovers spaces\par
\f2    \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Books directly\par
\f2    \f4\u8595?\f2  \f0 Reviews + builds community\par
```\par
\par
This is **asset-light, infinitely scalable, and deeply community-aligned.** You don't own the land. You own the network, the trust, and the discovery.\par
