# PART 11: FOUNDER MINDSET & EXECUTION PRINCIPLES\par
\par
These are the principles that should guide every decision made building CampIn.\par
\par
### 1. Community Before Commerce\par
Never prioritize a feature that helps revenue over one that builds community. Revenue follows community. Hipcamp was community first, revenue followed.\par
\par
### 2. Build in Public\par
Share the CampIn journey on Instagram. Show the platform being built. Show hosts being onboarded. Show the first bookings. People root for founders who are authentic. Hipcamp's mission was getting more people outside and promoting environmental stewardship. CampIn's mission is building India's outdoor culture. Say this, live it, show it.\par
\par
### 3. Do Things That Don't Scale\par
In the beginning, manually onboard every host with a phone call. Help them write their listing description. Take photos for them if needed. Be the best possible CampIn employee before you automate anything.\par
\par
### 4. Every Booking is Sacred in Year One\par
Handle every single booking personally. If something goes wrong, fix it immediately. Build a reputation that the camping community talks about in WhatsApp groups. That word-of-mouth is worth more than any ad budget.\par
\par
### 5. India First, Always\par
The design, language, price points, trust mechanisms, payment methods (UPI!), campsite types, and cultural references must all be deeply Indian. A Coorg farm stay is not a Tuscany farmhouse. Don't pretend it is. Celebrate what it is.\par
\par
### 6. Grow Like a Movement, Not a Startup\par
Make nature accessible to all \f2\emdash  that's Hipcamp's belief. CampIn's belief is: **Make India's outdoors accessible to every Indian.** Not just wealthy travelers. Not just Instagram-famous campers. Everyone. This mission, lived genuinely, is what will make CampIn irreplaceable.\par
